example.name: crc
example.brief: The CRC Example project is a demonstration program that uses the KSDK software to generate checksumsfor an ASCII string. Several CRC protocols are implemented using the CRC driver API.

example.name: dma_memory_to_memory
example.brief: The DMA memory to memory example is a simple demonstration program that uses the SDK software.It executes one shot transfer from source buffer to destination buffer using the SDK DMA drivers.The purpose of this example is to show how to use the DMA and to provide a simple example fordebugging and further development.

example.name: dma_wrap_transfer
example.brief: The DMA wrap transfer example is a simple demonstration program that uses the SDK software.It executes a wrap transfer from source buffer to destination buffer using the SDK DMA drivers.The purpose of this example is to show how to use the DMA wrap feature.

example.name: gpio_led_output
example.brief: The GPIO Example project is a demonstration program that uses the KSDK software to manipulate the general-purposeoutputs. The example use LEDs and buttons to demonstrates GPIO API for port and pin manipulation (init, set,clear, and toggle).

example.name: hello_world
example.brief: The HelloWorld demo prints the "Hello World" string to the terminal using the SDK UART drivers and repeat what user input. The purpose of this demo is to show how to use the UART, and to provide a simple project for debugging and further development.

example.name: led_blinky
example.brief: The LED Blinky demo application provides a sanity check for the new SDK build environments and board bring up. The LED Blinky demo uses the systick interrupt to realize the function of timing delay. The example takes turns to shine the LED. The purpose of this demo is to provide a simple project for debugging and further development.
